President Obama marked the holiday of Nowruz by extending his best wishes to those celebrating it in the United States and around the world. He emphasized the values of freedom of assembly, association, and expression, which are universal. He acknowledged the movements for change in the Middle East and North Africa and highlighted the Iranian government's failure to respect the rights of its people. He criticized the government's campaign of intimidation and abuse, including the persecution of prisoners of conscience, journalists, and religious minorities. President Obama expressed his support for the young people of Iran, who will shape the future of the country and help light the world. He closed with a quote from poet Simin Behbahani, calling for a season of second youth for all Iranians.